  "text": "Mathematically, we wish to define a single probability model that can apply to both parallel and monolingual data, and choose feature weights w that optimize the total likelihood of the parallel and monolingual data together. Probability models for word alignment of parallel data are one of the original problems studied in statistical machine translation . We wish to apply our log-linear feature-based model to parallel data, making the problem setting similar to that of [CITATION_1] . For simplicity, we assume a bag of words model that does not take into account the order of the words in the English sentence, resulting in a log-linear feature-based version of IBM Model 1.",
